1
00:02:02,546 --> 00:02:07,574
LIKE A CRASHED PLANE

2
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:18,827
Yes, in the morning I guess...
but I'm not sure yet...

3
00:02:19,664 --> 00:02:21,325
...yes...

4
00:02:22,133 --> 00:02:24,397
...when it stops raining I guess...

5
00:02:25,102 --> 00:02:28,094
I'll drop the bags
and go to the vet.

6
00:02:30,174 --> 00:02:31,835
Yes, I paid everything.

7
00:02:33,044 --> 00:02:35,808
Benito! Hello!
This is aunt Luchi.

8
00:02:36,947 --> 00:02:39,074
Hello! Listen, is Ani there?

9
00:02:40,918 --> 00:02:42,852
Yes, yes.
I'm bringing you a gift.

10
00:02:42,987 --> 00:02:45,455
Listen, can you
wake your mom up?

11
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:51,451
Something I made
for you, with shells.

12
00:02:52,496 --> 00:02:53,793
No, sea shells.

13
00:02:53,931 --> 00:02:55,523
I collected them.

14
00:02:59,070 --> 00:03:05,771
These shells have little holes,
then you tie them to a twig...

15
00:03:05,910 --> 00:03:08,538
...painted them
with granny's help.

16
00:03:09,980 --> 00:03:14,076
Ana, hello, how are you?
Yes, fine, everything's fine.

17
00:03:14,352 --> 00:03:16,445
Listen, sorry
my calling at this hour...

18
00:03:16,587 --> 00:03:18,612
I'll be quick because
this will cut off any moment.

19
00:03:18,756 --> 00:03:21,691
The plane was late. I don't think
I'll get there tomorrow...

20
00:03:21,826 --> 00:03:23,851
...in time to open the shop.
Can you go?

21
00:03:23,994 --> 00:03:27,327
- No, not now, I'm waiting...
- Great, great.

22
00:03:28,799 --> 00:03:30,994
- No, I already paid for it.
- No, no, because...

23
00:03:31,135 --> 00:03:34,366
- Oh! Wait... have you a coin?
- What?

24
00:03:34,505 --> 00:03:36,097
It's going to cut off...

25
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:38,067
- Yeah...
- Wait

26
00:03:39,510 --> 00:03:40,670
Ana?

27
00:03:43,481 --> 00:03:47,474
No, it cut off...
doesn't matter, thanks.

28
00:03:47,718 --> 00:03:49,379
- Bye.
- Bye.

29
00:05:21,846 --> 00:05:24,576
- Get out, Santi.
- I thought you'd died, dude.

30
00:05:25,649 --> 00:05:29,016
- I arrived yesterday, really late.
- This one's really good!

31
00:05:29,386 --> 00:05:30,876
Yeah, so is this one.

32
00:05:31,021 --> 00:05:34,115
Yes, it's the son.
Let's go for a walk?

33
00:05:34,391 --> 00:05:35,722
Okay, let's go.

34
00:05:48,105 --> 00:05:51,040
- So what d'you do in the end?
- Shall we play best of three?

35
00:05:51,509 --> 00:05:52,669
Let's.

36
00:05:54,445 --> 00:05:55,707
- Goal, dude.
- No way, pinwheel.

37
00:05:55,846 --> 00:05:57,507
No? Hell of a goal!

38
00:05:58,415 --> 00:06:00,815
Will you tell me what you
fixed up yesterday?

39
00:06:00,951 --> 00:06:03,511
- We're going to a rock concert.
- What are you going to see?

40
00:06:04,822 --> 00:06:07,086
I don't know.
I'm not going... no way!

41
00:06:07,424 --> 00:06:09,289
Didn't you say you liked her?

42
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,728
I lied, she's stupid.

43
00:06:12,963 --> 00:06:15,397
- Aren't you going
to let her know? - No.

44
00:06:16,033 --> 00:06:18,695
You, what,
any chicks in Valdivia?

45
00:06:18,836 --> 00:06:21,464
- I met one...
- So tell me about her.

46
00:06:22,439 --> 00:06:24,634
- What do you want to know?
- What she's like.

47
00:06:24,775 --> 00:06:27,539
What's her name,
where she lives, what she does...

48
00:06:29,013 --> 00:06:31,948
- She's pretty, she's cute.
- What else?

49
00:06:32,082 --> 00:06:34,448
That, that's the fun.
Come on! The ball!

50
00:06:34,585 --> 00:06:35,916
What's her name?

51
00:06:36,053 --> 00:06:39,545
- I don't know, come on! The ball!
- Wait... where does she live?

52
00:06:40,591 --> 00:06:41,888
I don't know.

53
00:06:42,459 --> 00:06:45,519
But you must have her phone,
you're going to see her again.

54
00:06:45,729 --> 00:06:49,495
- No, no, I haven't got it.
- But... you must be kidding...

55
00:06:49,733 --> 00:06:54,295
- Well, that's how I do things.
- You do things like an asshole.

56
00:06:54,438 --> 00:06:56,838
Hey look, it's a goal.
Serves you right... asshole.

57
00:07:14,725 --> 00:07:17,751
Here, feed it
and put it in a cage.

58
00:07:22,066 --> 00:07:23,328
What's it called?

59
00:07:23,467 --> 00:07:24,627
Arturo.

60
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:31,535
Hi, Arturo!

61
00:07:33,510 --> 00:07:35,603
Yes, I hope so, okay...

62
00:07:44,722 --> 00:07:47,953
Hello, yes, how are you.
I spoke to you the other day?

63
00:07:48,859 --> 00:07:51,419
Ah! The guy
I spoke to isn't there?

64
00:07:51,795 --> 00:07:54,559
Because he knows everything,
I already explained...

65
00:07:55,766 --> 00:07:56,960
...yes...

66
00:07:57,468 --> 00:08:00,835
Yes... about a house in Valdivia,
I don't want the gas cut off.

67
00:08:03,540 --> 00:08:04,507
No...

68
00:08:04,642 --> 00:08:07,702
...no, the thing is that
the holders can't sign.

69
00:08:09,380 --> 00:08:12,315
The other guy said he'd
fix things for me.

70
00:08:13,417 --> 00:08:16,352
Yes, I know... but now
I'm in charge, I could sign it...

71
00:08:17,821 --> 00:08:18,685
No...

72
00:08:18,822 --> 00:08:20,619
...no, it's impossible.

73
00:08:22,059 --> 00:08:22,889
Yes...

74
00:08:23,027 --> 00:08:26,861
No, all I can do is fax you
the holder's death certificate.

75
00:08:26,997 --> 00:08:29,761
I can send it to the subsidiary,
or to Valdivia, or...

76
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:33,097
...I can give it to you personally
but I sign.

77
00:08:36,040 --> 00:08:38,941
Yes, I know
my father was the holder.

78
00:08:39,410 --> 00:08:41,605
No, no,
my mother can't either.

79
00:09:37,568 --> 00:09:40,002
Nico,
can you bring Arturo?

80
00:09:51,782 --> 00:09:55,616
Here, Nico, go get some change
and give her the rabbit.

81
00:10:05,129 --> 00:10:08,360
Hi, Arturo!
I came to fetch you.

82
00:10:08,499 --> 00:10:10,899
"Hey, that's great.
I was already thinking...

83
00:10:11,034 --> 00:10:13,002
...you would leave me here."

84
00:10:13,137 --> 00:10:16,402
Where are you going
to get change?

85
00:10:16,540 --> 00:10:19,338
Because I live near from here
and I'm in a hurry.

86
00:10:19,476 --> 00:10:21,774
If you're going that side we can
go together and then I go on.

87
00:10:21,912 --> 00:10:23,106
What?

88
00:10:23,580 --> 00:10:25,946
I said if you're going that side,
we can go together...

89
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:28,517
Yes, yes, okay.

90
00:10:33,724 --> 00:10:36,090
When is the treatment over?

91
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:39,394
Monday is the last shot.

92
00:10:39,563 --> 00:10:40,860
Next Monday?

93
00:10:40,998 --> 00:10:42,056
Yes.

94
00:10:44,601 --> 00:10:46,000
What's wrong with it?

95
00:10:46,136 --> 00:10:48,001
It's a breathing problem.

96
00:10:48,739 --> 00:10:50,832
He needs some nebulizations.

97
00:10:53,477 --> 00:10:55,468
Look, there is a kiosk over there.

98
00:10:57,815 --> 00:11:01,615
"Oh, Luchi,
I missed you so much!"

99
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:18,024
He didn't have any...

100
00:11:19,603 --> 00:11:21,901
Since when have you had him?

101
00:11:22,706 --> 00:11:24,674
My sister gave it to me
a year ago.

102
00:11:24,808 --> 00:11:26,366
His name used to be Jorgelín.

103
00:11:26,510 --> 00:11:28,478
Do you remember when
you were called Jorgelín?

104
00:11:28,612 --> 00:11:33,640
"Ah, yes! What an ugly name.
Arturo is much nicer!"

105
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:38,517
I once had a dog.

106
00:11:41,525 --> 00:11:43,493
Yes, his name was Coco.

107
00:11:46,730 --> 00:11:49,324
His name was always Coco.
He was run over by a train.

108
00:11:49,466 --> 00:11:51,764
"Look, Luchi, there is
a flower shop over there."

109
00:11:51,902 --> 00:11:54,462
- D'you want me to go?
- Well, no... I'll go if you want.

110
00:11:54,605 --> 00:11:56,368
No, no, it's okay.
You hold Arturo.

111
00:11:56,506 --> 00:11:59,031
"When are you coming back,
Luchi?" Be right back.

112
00:12:06,917 --> 00:12:08,350
Thanks.

113
00:12:11,655 --> 00:12:12,713
Here.

114
00:12:12,856 --> 00:12:15,586
Ah... it was 20.

115
00:12:19,930 --> 00:12:21,488
Well, I'll go my way...

116
00:12:21,632 --> 00:12:23,293
- Okay, bye.
- Bye.

117
00:12:23,433 --> 00:12:25,367
- Bye, Arturo.
- "Bye, sir!"

118
00:12:25,502 --> 00:12:26,764
Not sir, Nico.

119
00:12:26,904 --> 00:12:29,634
"Bye, Nico.
Say hello to the rabbits."

120
00:12:29,773 --> 00:12:31,138
- Bye.
- Bye.

121
00:13:05,542 --> 00:13:07,737
These?
They're good!

122
00:13:08,111 --> 00:13:09,908
Say, what'll I do?

123
00:13:10,447 --> 00:13:12,438
I don't know, do something
so she'll have to come back...

124
00:13:12,582 --> 00:13:15,073
...just seeing her for a moment on
Monday at the vet isn't enough.

125
00:13:15,686 --> 00:13:17,119
What d'you think?

126
00:13:19,122 --> 00:13:21,682
Once you give the rabbit
the last shot, that's that?

127
00:13:22,092 --> 00:13:23,116
Yes...

128
00:13:23,660 --> 00:13:25,753
...unless it gets sick again.

129
00:13:26,029 --> 00:13:28,691
So, poison the rabbit.

130
00:13:29,533 --> 00:13:31,592
- Do I look good in these?
- Seriously, Santi, come on.

131
00:13:31,735 --> 00:13:33,635
I don't know, do something so
she comes back.

132
00:13:33,770 --> 00:13:35,328
That's all I can say.

133
00:14:02,099 --> 00:14:04,294
You guys, you going to
buy something or not?

134
00:14:04,434 --> 00:14:05,992
He wants to get a teddy bear
for his girlfriend.

135
00:14:06,136 --> 00:14:07,694
This.

136
00:15:23,113 --> 00:15:24,944
D'you want, would you
like something to drink?

137
00:15:25,582 --> 00:15:26,879
No, thanks.

138
00:15:27,150 --> 00:15:30,779
- The treatment is over, isn't it?
- Yes, I hope so. Besides...

139
00:15:30,921 --> 00:15:33,685
...it doesn't Arturo any good
to be out all the time.

140
00:15:34,558 --> 00:15:37,118
All the same, you don't
live far from here I think.

141
00:15:37,394 --> 00:15:40,557
No, about three blocks from
where we went for change.

142
00:15:40,931 --> 00:15:42,592
Will this take long?

143
00:15:43,934 --> 00:15:46,994
No, I don't think so.
It must be over by now.

144
00:15:47,604 --> 00:15:50,437
- Why, you have to work today?
- No, I'm not working today.

145
00:15:51,775 --> 00:15:55,541
- You have to go to college?
- No, but I've a lot to study.

146
00:16:01,418 --> 00:16:03,045
- There it's over.
- How is he?

147
00:16:03,787 --> 00:16:06,915
- A bit low.
- He's very weak, Arturo.

148
00:16:07,324 --> 00:16:10,919
"Yes, I feel very dizzy,
let's go home, please!"

149
00:16:11,461 --> 00:16:13,691
- How much is it?
- Forty five.

150
00:16:15,365 --> 00:16:17,356
Here, Nico, you take the money,
give her those...

151
00:16:17,501 --> 00:16:19,492
...antibiotics over there,
behind the cash register.

152
00:16:20,470 --> 00:16:22,995
Okay, now just keep an eye
on him, see how he gets along.

153
00:16:23,140 --> 00:16:25,370
He might be a little low the first
few days, it's normal.

154
00:16:25,509 --> 00:16:27,704
But don't worry,
he'll get over it.

155
00:16:30,981 --> 00:16:32,915
Well, I'm leaving,
I have a lot of work to do.

156
00:16:33,049 --> 00:16:34,573
Thank you, bye.

157
00:16:37,921 --> 00:16:41,755
Take this, it's all inside.
I put a bunny inside, for Arturo.

158
00:16:41,892 --> 00:16:44,520
"Ah! That's nice, thank you!"

159
00:16:44,661 --> 00:16:47,323
- Bye.
- Bye. Bye, Arturo.

160
00:16:47,464 --> 00:16:48,522
"Bye".

161
00:17:28,939 --> 00:17:31,305
- You think I mustn't call her?
- How are you going to call her!

162
00:17:31,441 --> 00:17:33,102
If you call somebody to
give them back the money...

163
00:17:33,376 --> 00:17:36,504
...is either because you like her
or you're dumb. Let her call you.

164
00:17:36,980 --> 00:17:40,541
- What if she doesn't call?
- It's fifty bucks. She'll call.

165
00:17:41,484 --> 00:17:43,111
Here, have some.

166
00:17:45,121 --> 00:17:47,055
- What is it?
- Peanuts.

167
00:17:49,159 --> 00:17:51,719
- You didn't pay for it!
- Then don't eat!

168
00:17:52,062 --> 00:17:53,324
You're an asshole.

169
00:17:53,463 --> 00:17:55,590
You call me an asshole but
you stole from the girl you like.

170
00:17:55,732 --> 00:17:58,724
- I'm going to give her the money.
- Yeah, that's how I started.

171
00:18:08,578 --> 00:18:10,876
We've been here
for more than two hours.

172
00:18:11,047 --> 00:18:14,312
- Why don't we go to my place?
- I'll stay a little longer.

173
00:18:14,517 --> 00:18:15,711
Doing what?

174
00:18:16,086 --> 00:18:17,815
Nothing, dude.

175
00:18:17,954 --> 00:18:19,785
After that, you going home?

176
00:18:19,923 --> 00:18:22,619
No, Enrique is staying with
my mother. I'll stay here.

177
00:18:24,694 --> 00:18:27,720
- Come on, let's go to my place.
- I don't want to go to your place.

178
00:18:27,864 --> 00:18:30,924
- Did you fix your bedroom wall?
- Not yet.

179
00:18:31,468 --> 00:18:33,402
But you can sleep on a mattress
in the living room floor.

180
00:18:33,536 --> 00:18:35,697
I won't sleep well that way.

181
00:18:39,142 --> 00:18:41,406
Do as you please.
Come over later if you want to.

182
00:18:42,646 --> 00:18:44,671
- Okay.
- Bye.

183
00:18:47,684 --> 00:18:50,016
Don't go stealing things
on the way.

184
00:18:50,387 --> 00:18:51,877
Bye, man!

185
00:19:19,482 --> 00:19:20,676
Hello!

186
00:19:21,618 --> 00:19:23,381
Ah! Hello.

187
00:19:24,321 --> 00:19:26,289
You're still there!

188
00:19:27,724 --> 00:19:29,419
Let me see, hold on.

189
00:19:37,767 --> 00:19:39,394
The gas bill?

190
00:19:39,936 --> 00:19:43,531
It was paid on March 14 of 2002.

191
00:19:45,108 --> 00:19:46,803
It's all right.

192
00:19:47,610 --> 00:19:49,578
What time you coming back?

193
00:19:50,780 --> 00:19:54,079
Yes, well, yes, I'll stay.
No problem.

194
00:19:55,051 --> 00:19:57,986
Hey, you forgot to buy
the ventilator that broke.

195
00:19:59,856 --> 00:20:00,914
Okay.

196
00:20:01,057 --> 00:20:02,422
Bye.

197
00:20:08,832 --> 00:20:12,666
Did you know that Fran hangs
with my father's friends...

198
00:20:12,802 --> 00:20:14,895
...to play squash and have dinner?

199
00:20:15,038 --> 00:20:16,471
How come?

200
00:20:17,741 --> 00:20:19,641
Where does he know them from?

201
00:20:19,909 --> 00:20:23,401
Julio, the one he plays with,
he met him in Valdivia...

202
00:20:23,646 --> 00:20:25,580
...and the rest he knows
them from the club.

203
00:20:25,715 --> 00:20:28,115
We used to spend
summer holidays together.

204
00:20:28,385 --> 00:20:29,977
Sounds hilarious.

205
00:20:30,487 --> 00:20:32,546
He used to go every weekend.

206
00:20:33,056 --> 00:20:35,786
I don't know... it seems...
it's odd.

207
00:20:37,394 --> 00:20:39,624
- Are you jealous?
- No.

208
00:20:49,005 --> 00:20:50,495
What's that you're taking?

209
00:20:50,640 --> 00:20:52,835
Don't know,
stole them from mom.

210
00:20:54,744 --> 00:20:56,371
- Want some?
- No.

211
00:21:03,953 --> 00:21:05,443
Hello.

212
00:21:06,389 --> 00:21:08,653
Forty-eight pesos.

213
00:21:12,629 --> 00:21:14,358
Have you got your ID?

214
00:21:14,497 --> 00:21:15,964
I think I forgot it.

215
00:21:18,468 --> 00:21:20,698
Why don't you
have another look?

216
00:21:24,407 --> 00:21:26,500
No, I haven't got it.

217
00:21:26,709 --> 00:21:29,576
You know me.
I always come here.

218
00:21:29,779 --> 00:21:32,339
It's a gift for him,
it's his birthday.

219
00:21:35,552 --> 00:21:36,883
You're Enrique?

220
00:21:37,020 --> 00:21:39,488
Yeah.
What's my name?

221
00:21:41,024 --> 00:21:42,389
Enrique.

222
00:21:43,193 --> 00:21:44,626
See?

223
00:22:06,149 --> 00:22:08,549
- Happy birthday.
- Thank you.

224
00:22:08,685 --> 00:22:10,710
- Happy birthday, pal!
- Get out, you moron!

225
00:22:10,854 --> 00:22:12,082
Bye, thanks.

226
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:19,355
- Hi, there.
- How are you.

227
00:22:19,662 --> 00:22:20,924
Take this.

228
00:22:21,431 --> 00:22:23,956
- What is it?
- Chocolate, for you.

229
00:22:24,734 --> 00:22:25,860
Thank you.

230
00:22:26,002 --> 00:22:27,333
What, are they imported?

231
00:22:27,470 --> 00:22:29,404
Yes,
it was well worth the effort.

232
00:22:29,672 --> 00:22:32,072
Shut up!
What, are you funny now?

233
00:22:33,409 --> 00:22:35,969
- What's wrong with him?
- He's sleepy.

234
00:22:37,580 --> 00:22:41,016
- Your mom? How is she?
- Same as always.

235
00:22:41,384 --> 00:22:44,512
- Is she home already?
- Yes, Enrique's looking after her.

236
00:22:48,625 --> 00:22:49,887
Don't you want
anything to drink?

237
00:22:50,026 --> 00:22:52,324
No, he doesn't want anything.
Did you call the plumber?

238
00:22:52,462 --> 00:22:54,589
No, I didn't have time.
I was all day after the gas thing.

239
00:22:54,731 --> 00:22:57,666
Yes, I know, but my bedroom
wall is dripping all over.

240
00:22:57,800 --> 00:22:59,700
Well, I can't be
in charge of everything!

241
00:22:59,836 --> 00:23:01,599
But you do take care of things in
Valdivia. My bedroom wall...

242
00:23:01,738 --> 00:23:03,603
...waters for two weeks and you
didn't even pick up the phone.

243
00:23:03,740 --> 00:23:05,264
The house needs
to be taken care of.

244
00:23:05,408 --> 00:23:07,706
We never go there,
why don't we just rent it?

245
00:23:07,844 --> 00:23:09,903
This isn't the right time
to talk about this, see?

246
00:23:10,046 --> 00:23:11,809
I've got to go to work,
my ears hurt.

247
00:23:11,948 --> 00:23:14,109
Go see the doctor
if your ears hurt.

248
00:23:23,159 --> 00:23:25,024
Drop it! You're going to set
the whole house on fire!

249
00:23:25,161 --> 00:23:28,062
Nico, this isn't the right time
to talk about this, see?

250
00:23:29,632 --> 00:23:31,327
Fuck you, asshole!

251
00:23:42,879 --> 00:23:44,369
Veterinary.

252
00:23:46,916 --> 00:23:49,384
Oh, yes.
How are you?

253
00:23:52,522 --> 00:23:54,547
No, frankly I have no idea.

254
00:23:57,760 --> 00:24:00,661
